wiki.content: Dubbed “the best song” made by Baby Pluto since Lil Uzi Vert introduced their alter ego, “Baby Pluto” serves as the introduction to Uzi’s long-awaited sophomore studio album, Eternal Atake. The track is also the opener to the “Baby Pluto” third of Eternal Atake. The aggressive banger energetically kicks off the project with a triumphant vibe, with Uzi rapping a monotone manner instead using their traditional melodic vocals. Uzi is very braggadocios on the song, flexing their sexual prowess and materialistic wealth all over the track while reasserting their position on top of the game. The instrumental is based on that of Uzi’s unreleased 2017 throwaway “Fast as You Can” produced by Ike Beatz. Read more on Last.fm.
